{"id": 5061, "title": "Ticket #5061: Accept alternate Globus thread models", "description": "<blockquote>\nOSG has observed a case where Condor's attempt to use the GSI libraries failed because it couldn't set Globus to not use pthreads. Using pthreads isn't a problem, just tiny performance hit, so this shouldn't cause a failure.\n\n<p>Details are here:\n<a class=\"external\" href=\"https://ticket.opensciencegrid.org/24806\">https://ticket.opensciencegrid.org/24806</a></p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2015-May-21 16:25:19 by bbockelm:</em> <br/>\n\nIn particular - the difference between the compiled globus and the (newer) runtime globus was causing the globus_module_activate code to <em>force</em> pthread mode.  So, HTCondor had no choice - it was forced to use pthreads.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jul-02 13:06</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=45203\">[45203]</a></span>: update 8.2.9 version history items with edited versions of same items that come from the 8.3.6 and 8.3.7 versions, as release ordering caused replication of these items <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=5114\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5114'); return false;\" title=\"job_dagman_abort-final-A consistently fails on Windows\">#5114</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=5061\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5061'); return false;\" title=\"Accept alternate Globus thread models\">#5061</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=5080\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5080'); return fals